# Day 21 – 3D Printable One-Part Molds

## What I built
Designed a one-part open-face mold in Fusion 360, suitable for casting simple shapes. The mold includes a cavity, draft angles for clean part release, and a flat parting surface.

## Techniques used
- Offset curve (sketch tool)
- Draft angle on extruded walls
- Shell tool for cavity creation
- Sketch text / decal placement
- 3D print orientation planning

## Key rules learned
- One-part molds work only for shapes with no undercuts — the part must lift straight out
- Draft angles (1–3°) on vertical walls prevent the cast part from locking inside the mold
- Shell thickness must be sufficient to resist casting pressure without warping
- Design the mold so the open face is on top during printing to avoid support material inside the cavity

## Time taken
20 min

